com.orange.api.ons.provisioning
Class ONSProvisioning

java.lang.Object
  com.orange.api.ons.provisioning.ONSProvisioning

public class ONSProvisioning
extends java.lang.Object

ONS provisioning helper. Allows to

  • create a GS1 subscriber's zones using its Global Company Prefix (GCP) and associated GS1/EPCglobal identification schemes (SGLN, SGTIN, SSCC, GIAI, etc) using CreateCompany(String, String, String, String, String) function,
  • and to import a company's catalog (such as a GTIN-based product catalog) as NAPTR and TXT entries into ONS and associated EPCIS, using ImportCompanyCatalog(String, String, String, String, String, HashMap).

Author:
Marc-Antoine Mouilleron, Orange Labs (marcantoine.mouilleron@orange-ftgroup.com)

ImportCompanyCatalog

public static boolean ImportCompanyCatalog(java.lang.String file,
                                           java.lang.String ONSlocal,
                                           java.lang.String ParentONS,
                                           java.lang.String serviceType,
                                           java.lang.String serviceURL,
                                           java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> importparams)
                                    throws java.lang.Exception
Imports a company's product catalog and creates associated TXT and NAPTR entries to serviceType/serviceURL. As an option, also attemps to import into associated EPCIS's MasterData.

Parameters:
file - Full pathname to file (e.g. c:\temp\12345.csv).
Right format for input file is like 
GS1Type,EPCManagerLength,Value,Name,Attributes
GLN-96,8,3011875700107,CAFES MALONGO,
SSCC-96,6,031875700000000009,SSCC,
GRAI-96,6,031875700000090,RETURNABLE,
GTIN-96,6,03187571101903,123 SPRESSO GRANDE RESERVE,EAN DISPATCH UNIT:03187571201900;WEIGHT:78g;
ONSlocal - IP address of local ONS
ParentONS - Root naming (e.g. onsepc.eu)
serviceType - Service type (e.g. EPC+epcis)
serviceURL - Service URL (e.g. http://mycompany.com/epcis)
importparams - hash map of import parameters.
List of parameters include:
  • "wings","true" for Wings-like notation (dotted)
  • "epcisMasterdata","true" for importing associated vocabulary onto EPCIS's MasterData
  • "user","<user>" and "password","<password>" for local ONS's SSH remote access
Returns:
true if import is successful.
Note: unreadable lines of the input file will be ignored, whereas function will still return true. Existing entries will not be updated.
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
